The Accessible Object class is the base class for Field , Method and Constructor objects . It provides the ability to flag a reflected object as suppressing default Java language access control checks when it is used . The access checks -- for public , default ( package ) access , protected , and private members -- are performed when Fields , Methods or Constructors are used to set or get fields , to invoke methods , or to create and initialize new instances of classes , respectively .
